r=\sqrt {x^2+y^2}
\phi
\psi
\phi=\frac{\pi}{2}-t
\psi=\pi-t
\left(\frac{x}{a}\right)^2+\left(\frac{y}{b}\right)^2=r^2
x=acos(t),y=bsin(t)
r=\sqrt{x^2+y^2}=\sqrt{a^2cos^2(t)+b^2sin^2(t)}\text{, where "t" is the angle from }0\text{ to }2\pi.
r=\sqrt{a^2cos^2(\pi-\psi)+b^2sin^2(\frac{\pi}{2}-\phi)}
